          <span class="breadcrumb-current">Settings & Security</span>
        </nav>

        <!-- Page Title -->
        <h1 class="doc-page-title" id="csec_title">Settings & Security</h1>
        <p class="doc-page-subtitle">
          Learn how to configure your MPay Consumer Wallet settings, manage security preferences, 
          enable biometric authentication, and protect your account with advanced security features.
        </p>

        <!-- Security Visual -->
        <div class="security-visual">
          <div class="security-visual-icon">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-shield-halved"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="security-visual-content">
            <h4>Your Security Matters</h4>
            <p>MPay uses bank-grade encryption and multiple security layers to keep your wallet and transactions safe. Configure these settings to maximize your protection.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section: PIN Management -->
        <section class="doc-section" id="csec_content_pin">
          <h2 class="doc-section-title" id="section-pin">PIN Management</h2>
          <p>
            Your transaction PIN is a 6-digit code used to authorize payments and sensitive account operations. 
            It is separate from your device lock screen and provides an additional layer of security.
          </p>

          <h4>Setting Your PIN</h4>
          <p>When you first set up your MPay wallet, you'll be prompted to create a transaction PIN. Follow these steps:</p>

          <div class="steps">
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-title">Navigate to Security Settings</div>
              <div class="step-desc">Open the app menu and tap <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Security</strong> → <strong>Transaction PIN</strong>.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-title">Enter a 6-Digit PIN</div>
              <div class="step-desc">Choose a PIN that you can remember but that isn't easily guessable. Avoid sequential numbers like <code>123456</code> or repeated digits like <code>111111</code>.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-title">Confirm Your PIN</div>
              <div class="step-desc">Re-enter your PIN to confirm. The system will verify both entries match before saving.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-title">PIN Saved Successfully</div>
              <div class="step-desc">Your PIN is now active. You'll use it to approve transactions, transfers, and account changes.</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h4>Changing Your PIN</h4>
          <p>To change your existing PIN, you'll need to verify your current PIN first:</p>

          <div class="steps">
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-title">Go to Settings → Security → Change PIN</div>
              <div class="step-desc">Navigate to the PIN management section in your security settings.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-title">Enter Current PIN</div>
              <div class="step-desc">Verify your identity by entering your current 6-digit PIN.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-title">Enter & Confirm New PIN</div>
              <div class="step-desc">Type your new PIN and confirm it. Your new PIN takes effect immediately.</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="callout callout-warning">
            <div class="callout-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-triangle-exclamation"></i></div>
            <div class="callout-content">
              <strong>PIN Security Tips</strong>
              <p>Never share your PIN with anyone, including MPay support staff. MPay will never ask you for your PIN via phone, email, or SMS. After 5 failed PIN attempts, your account will be temporarily locked for 30 minutes.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h4>Forgot Your PIN?</h4>
          <p>
            If you forget your transaction PIN, tap <strong>"Forgot PIN"</strong> on the PIN entry screen. 
            You'll need to verify your identity through your registered email or phone number to reset it.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Section: Biometric Authentication -->
        <section class="doc-section" id="csec_content_biometric">
          <h2 class="doc-section-title" id="section-biometric">Biometric Authentication</h2>
          <p>
            Enable fingerprint or Face ID authentication for quick and secure access to your wallet. 
            Biometric login adds convenience while maintaining strong security.
          </p>

          <div class="method-cards">
            <div class="method-card">
              <div class="method-card-icon">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-fingerprint"></i>
              </div>
              <h5>Fingerprint</h5>
              <p>Use your registered fingerprint for fast wallet access and transaction approval.</p>
              <span class="recommended-badge">Most Common</span>
            </div>
            <div class="method-card">
              <div class="method-card-icon">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-face-smile"></i>
              </div>
              <h5>Face ID</h5>
              <p>Authenticate with facial recognition for a seamless hands-free experience.</p>
              <span class="recommended-badge">Recommended</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h4>Enabling Biometric Login</h4>
          <div class="steps">
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-title">Open Security Settings</div>
              <div class="step-desc">Go to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Security</strong> → <strong>Biometric Authentication</strong>.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-title">Toggle Biometric Login</div>
              <div class="step-desc">Turn on the biometric authentication toggle. Your device must have at least one fingerprint or Face ID enrolled.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-title">Verify with PIN</div>
              <div class="step-desc">Enter your transaction PIN to confirm the change. This ensures only you can enable biometrics.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-title">Test Your Biometric</div>
              <div class="step-desc">You'll be prompted to scan your fingerprint or face to verify it works correctly.</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="toggle-demo">
            <div class="toggle-switch active" role="switch" aria-checked="true" aria-label="Biometric login" tabindex="0"></div>
            <span class="toggle-label">Biometric Login for Wallet Access</span>
          </div>
          <div class="toggle-demo">
            <div class="toggle-switch" role="switch" aria-checked="false" aria-label="Biometric for transactions" tabindex="0"></div>
            <span class="toggle-label">Biometric Approval for Transactions</span>
          </div>

          <div class="callout callout-info">
            <div class="callout-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i></div>
            <div class="callout-content">
              <strong>Device Requirements</strong>
              <p>Biometric authentication requires a compatible device with enrolled biometrics. If your device doesn't support biometrics, this option will be unavailable. You can always fall back to PIN authentication.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section: Two-Factor Authentication -->
        <section class="doc-section" id="csec_content_2fa">
          <h2 class="doc-section-title" id="section-2fa">Two-Factor Authentication</h2>
          <p>
            Two-factor authentication (2FA) adds an extra verification step when logging in from a new device 
            or performing high-value transactions. We strongly recommend enabling 2FA for maximum account security.
          </p>

          <span class="security-badge"><i class="fa-solid fa-check-circle"></i> Strongly Recommended</span>

          <h4>Available 2FA Methods</h4>
          <div class="method-cards">
            <div class="method-card">
              <div class="method-card-icon">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-mobile-screen-button"></i>
              </div>
              <h5>SMS Verification</h5>
              <p>Receive a one-time code via SMS to your registered phone number.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="method-card">
              <div class="method-card-icon">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-key"></i>
              </div>
              <h5>Authenticator App</h5>
              <p>Use Google Authenticator, Authy, or any TOTP-compatible app.</p>
              <span class="recommended-badge">Most Secure</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h4>Setting Up 2FA with Authenticator App</h4>
          <div class="steps">
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-title">Navigate to 2FA Settings</div>
              <div class="step-desc">Go to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Security</strong> → <strong>Two-Factor Authentication</strong>.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-title">Select Authenticator App</div>
              <div class="step-desc">Choose "Authenticator App" as your 2FA method.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-title">Scan QR Code</div>
              <div class="step-desc">Open your authenticator app and scan the displayed QR code. If you can't scan, use the manual setup key provided.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-title">Enter Verification Code</div>
              <div class="step-desc">Enter the 6-digit code from your authenticator app to verify the setup.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-title">Save Backup Codes</div>
              <div class="step-desc">Download and securely store your backup codes. These can be used if you lose access to your authenticator app.</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="callout callout-danger">
            <div class="callout-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-exclamation"></i></div>
            <div class="callout-content">
              <strong>Save Your Backup Codes</strong>
              <p>Store backup codes in a safe, offline location. If you lose access to your authenticator app and don't have backup codes, you'll need to contact support with identity verification to regain access. This process can take 24-48 hours.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section: Notification Settings -->
        <section class="doc-section" id="csec_content_notifications">
          <h2 class="doc-section-title" id="section-notifications">Notification Settings</h2>
          <p>
            Configure how and when MPay sends you alerts about transactions, security events, and account activity. 
            Keeping notifications enabled helps you monitor your account in real time.
          </p>

          <h4>Available Notification Channels</h4>
          <div class="settings-card">
            <div class="settings-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-bell"></i></div>
            <div class="settings-card-content">
              <h5>Push Notifications</h5>
              <p>Real-time alerts delivered directly to your device. Recommended for transaction alerts and security notifications.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="settings-card">
            <div class="settings-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-envelope"></i></div>
            <div class="settings-card-content">
              <h5>Email Notifications</h5>
              <p>Detailed notifications sent to your registered email address. Includes transaction receipts and monthly summaries.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="settings-card">
            <div class="settings-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-comment-sms"></i></div>
            <div class="settings-card-content">
              <h5>SMS Alerts</h5>
              <p>Critical alerts via text message. Used for high-value transactions and security events when push is unavailable.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h4>Configurable Alert Types</h4>
          <ul class="option-list">
            <li>
              <i class="fa-solid fa-check"></i>
              <span><strong>Transaction Alerts</strong> — Every payment sent or received</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <i class="fa-solid fa-check"></i>
              <span><strong>Security Alerts</strong> — Login attempts, device changes, password resets</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <i class="fa-solid fa-check"></i>
              <span><strong>Balance Alerts</strong> — When balance drops below your set threshold</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <i class="fa-solid fa-check"></i>
              <span><strong>Promotional</strong> — News, offers, and feature announcements</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <i class="fa-solid fa-check"></i>
              <span><strong>Weekly Summary</strong> — Weekly spending and activity digest</span>
            </li>
          </ul>

          <div class="callout callout-success">
            <div class="callout-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-lightbulb"></i></div>
            <div class="callout-content">
              <strong>Pro Tip</strong>
              <p>We recommend keeping <strong>Transaction Alerts</strong> and <strong>Security Alerts</strong> enabled at all times. These help you quickly detect unauthorized activity on your account.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h4>Managing Notifications</h4>
          <p>
            To adjust your notification preferences, navigate to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Notifications</strong>. 
            Use the toggles to enable or disable each notification type per channel. Changes take effect immediately.
          </p>

          <div class="toggle-demo">
            <div class="toggle-switch active" role="switch" aria-checked="true" aria-label="Transaction alerts" tabindex="0"></div>
            <span class="toggle-label">Transaction Alerts (Push)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="toggle-demo">
            <div class="toggle-switch active" role="switch" aria-checked="true" aria-label="Security alerts" tabindex="0"></div>
            <span class="toggle-label">Security Alerts (Push + Email)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="toggle-demo">
            <div class="toggle-switch" role="switch" aria-checked="false" aria-label="Promotional notifications" tabindex="0"></div>
            <span class="toggle-label">Promotional Notifications</span>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section: Privacy Settings -->
        <section class="doc-section" id="csec_content_privacy">
          <h2 class="doc-section-title" id="section-privacy">Privacy Settings</h2>
          <p>
            MPay gives you full control over your personal data and privacy preferences. 
            Manage how your information is used, shared, and stored.
          </p>

          <h4>Privacy Controls</h4>
          <div class="privacy-grid">
            <div class="privacy-option">
              <div class="privacy-option-title">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-eye-slash"></i> Profile Visibility
              </div>
              <div class="privacy-option-desc">Control who can see your display name and profile picture when sending or receiving payments.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="privacy-option">
              <div class="privacy-option-title">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-chart-simple"></i> Analytics & Usage Data
              </div>
              <div class="privacy-option-desc">Choose whether to share anonymized usage data to help improve the MPay experience.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="privacy-option">
              <div class="privacy-option-title">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-location-dot"></i> Location Data
              </div>
              <div class="privacy-option-desc">Manage location access. Used for fraud detection and nearby merchant features.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="privacy-option">
              <div class="privacy-option-title">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-address-book"></i> Contacts Access
              </div>
              <div class="privacy-option-desc">Allow MPay to access your contacts for easy P2P transfers. Fully optional.</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h4>Data Management</h4>
          <p>You have the right to access, export, and delete your personal data at any time:</p>

          <ul class="option-list">
            <li>
              <i class="fa-solid fa-download"></i>
              <span><strong>Export Data</strong> — Download a copy of all your personal data and transaction history</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <i class="fa-solid fa-clock-rotate-left"></i>
              <span><strong>Activity Log</strong> — Review a complete log of account activity and access events</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <i class="fa-solid fa-trash-can"></i>
              <span><strong>Delete Account</strong> — Permanently delete your account and all associated data</span>
            </li>
          </ul>

          <div class="callout callout-warning">
            <div class="callout-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-triangle-exclamation"></i></div>
            <div class="callout-content">
              <strong>Account Deletion</strong>
              <p>Account deletion is permanent and cannot be undone. Before deleting, ensure your wallet balance is zero and all pending transactions are completed. Regulatory requirements may require us to retain certain transaction records for up to 7 years.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h4>Privacy Policy</h4>
          <p>
            For complete details on how MPay collects, uses, and protects your data, please review our 
            <a onclick="load_page('privacy_policy')" tabindex="0" style="color: var(--color-primary, #2563eb); cursor: pointer; text-decoration: underline;">Privacy Policy</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Section: FAQ -->
        <section class="doc-section faq-section" id="csec_faq_accordion">
          <h2 class="doc-section-title" id="section-faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-1">
              <span>What happens if I forget my transaction PIN?</span>
              <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down faq-chevron"></i>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-1" role="region">
              <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                Tap "Forgot PIN" on the PIN entry screen. You'll need to verify your identity through your registered email or phone number. A PIN reset link will be sent to you. After verification, you can set a new 6-digit PIN. Your account may be temporarily restricted during the reset process for security.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-2">
              <span>Can I use both fingerprint and Face ID?</span>
              <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down faq-chevron"></i>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-2" role="region">
              <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                You can only use the biometric method supported by your device. Most devices support either fingerprint or Face ID, not both simultaneously. If your device supports both, you can choose which one to use as your primary biometric method in the security settings.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-3">
              <span>How do I recover my account if I lose my 2FA device?</span>
              <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down faq-chevron"></i>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-3" role="region">
              <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                Use one of your backup codes to log in and disable 2FA. If you don't have backup codes, contact MPay support with your registered email and a government-issued ID for identity verification. The recovery process typically takes 24-48 hours for security reasons.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-4">
              <span>Why am I not receiving push notifications?</span>
              <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down faq-chevron"></i>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-4" role="region">
              <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                First, check that notifications are enabled in both the MPay app settings and your device's system settings. On Android, ensure the app isn't being restricted by battery optimization. On iOS, check the Notification Center settings. If notifications still aren't working, try logging out and back in, or reinstalling the app.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-5">
              <span>Can I download my transaction history?</span>
              <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down faq-chevron"></i>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-5" role="region">
              <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                Yes! Go to <strong>Settings → Privacy → Export Data</strong> to download a complete copy of your transaction history. You can export in CSV or PDF format. The export will be sent to your registered email address and typically arrives within a few minutes.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-6">
              <span>Is my PIN stored on MPay servers?</span>
              <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down faq-chevron"></i>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-6" role="region">
              <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                No. Your PIN is never stored in plain text. MPay uses strong one-way hashing (bcrypt) to store a hashed version of your PIN. This means even MPay employees cannot see your actual PIN. All PIN verification happens securely server-side by comparing hashes.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Prev/Next Navigation -->
        <nav class="doc-pagination" id="csec_prev_next" aria-label="Page navigation">
          <a class="doc-pagination-link prev" onclick="load_page('consumer_p2p_transfers')" tabindex="0" role="link">
            <span class="doc-pagination-label">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-left"></i> Previous
            </span>
            <span class="doc-pagination-title">P2P Transfers</span>
          </a>
          <a class="doc-pagination-link next" onclick="load_page('consumer_troubleshooting')" tabindex="0" role="link">
